Defendant Brad C Hardtke in court with Attorney James R Donohoo.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State files an amended information.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #2 on amended information and an alford plea to Count #3 on amended information.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Counts #2 & 3.  Count #1 is dismissed outright.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Donohoo makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements. Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #2:  WITHHELD SENTENCE

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR    (3 days credit, if revoked)    *May terminate after 6 months, if deemed appropriate by agent*

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribed/sign releases.
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____No violent contact with: Heather P. 
____Domestic Violence Counseling through a State Certified Batterers Intervention Program such as Alliance Counseling or Family Services of Waukesha;

COSTS:  $243.00 & $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted and remainder to be returned to poster)

**Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.**

CONDITION TIME:  20 Days, Non-working hours with standard release conditions - STAYED - to be used at agent's discretion.


